# East–West Route, Warsaw

The East–West Route (, Trasa W-Z) is a major thoroughfare  in Warsaw, Poland, that joins Praga in the east  with the city center, going through Muranów and out to Wola in the west.
It was one of the first major post-World War II infrastructure projects, carried out during 1947-1949.
